      "message": "In general, std::function can\u0027t inline away as well as this sort of implementation can.  It hinges on the size of the function\u0027s closure and the whims of the std::function implementation. \n This style as written is a lot more predictable in terms of inlining and calls to malloc (yes, it will inline, with no calls to malloc).\n\nIt\u0027s usually best to stick to std::function only where you need its type erasure.",
